title: NASA: Cygnus on track for Tuesday morning arrival at the International Space Station
summary: Northrop Grumman engineers were able to create a new burn plan for the spacecraft after it missed two attempts to perform its “targeted altitude burn.” Capture using the robotic Canadarm2 is anticipated for about 3:10 a.m. EDT (0710 UTC) on Tuesday, Aug. 6.
